id: pm-96vo
title: "GH-526: aggregate --sum/--avg accept unknown field names and silently report 0"
description: "GH-526 (2026-07-12, repro with --no-extensions on 2026.7.12): pm aggregate --group-by validates its argument against a known field list and fails fast, but --sum/--avg accept any string and silently emit sum:0 / omit avg with null_count==count as the only signal. A realistic typo (--sum estimated_minute) pastes a silently-wrong 0 into governance reports. Fix: validate --sum/--avg field names against the summable-numeric domain (built-ins + registered numeric custom fields) with the existing Invalid-argument-value error shape; if free-form custom fields must stay allowed, emit an explicit unknown_field marker/warning when the field resolves to zero known occurrences. Sibling contrast: pm-bvns shipped the aggregation feature itself (closed — do not touch). Same fail-fast-over-silent-success principle as the dep colon-shorthand fix (pm-zazb)."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,aggregate,cli,gh-issue,validation
created_at: "2026-07-12T18:52:48.595Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T15:33:41.238Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-13T15:32:51.854Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "Unknown --sum/--avg field names are rejected with the same 'Invalid argument value' error shape as --group-by, listing known numeric fields including registered numeric custom fields; valid built-in and custom numeric fields keep aggregating; spec covers the estimated_minute typo case producing a hard error instead of sum:0; docs/contracts updated if help text changes"
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: Resolved by validating aggregate numeric fields against built-ins plus runtime schema number definitions.
expected_result: Typos fail fast and registered numeric custom fields remain fully aggregatable.
actual_result: "estimated_minutez returns usage exit 2; built-in and custom sum/avg/null cases pass unit, acceptance, and installed-package proof."
